# ====================================================================
# FILAHA BACKEND — AGENT RULES
# ====================================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 1: READ BEFORE YOU CODE (MANDATORY)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Before making ANY changes, read these two files IN ORDER:
#
# 1. PROJECT_CONTEXT.txt  → Project description, tech stack, ethical
#    pillars, language rules, DB architecture, AI response format.
#    ALSO check "SECTION 9: PROJECT STATUS LOG" at the bottom —
#    it tells you where the project currently stands and what was
#    last changed.
#
# 2. WALKTHROUGH.md       → Full system workflow, folder-by-folder
#    build order (Phase 0-9), data flows for MAÏ and SILA,
#    how to run/test each script, and the request lifecycle.
#    Use this to understand which phase you are in and what
#    comes next.
#
# Together these files give you the full picture. Do NOT start
# coding until you understand the current project state.

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 2: CODING RULES
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# - Default UI language: Arabic (MSA / العربية الفصحى). No Darija.
# - Code language (variables, comments, file names): English ONLY.
# - Every AI feature must include explainability logging
#   (confidence, factors, data_sources_used — see AI response format
#   in PROJECT_CONTEXT.txt section 8).
# - Every file contains a top comment explaining what the file does.
# - Every folder has a "whatFor.txt" explaining its role in the project.
# - Follow the build order in WALKTHROUGH.md — do not skip phases.

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 3: UPDATE PROJECT STATUS (MANDATORY — WHEN DONE)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# When you finish your session, you MUST update "SECTION 9: PROJECT
# STATUS LOG" at the bottom of PROJECT_CONTEXT.txt. Add a new entry
# with:
#
#   ### [DATE] — [SHORT TITLE]
#   - **Phase:** Which phase (0-9) the project is at now
#   - **What was done:** Bullet list of files created/modified
#   - **What works now:** What can be tested/run after your changes
#   - **Next step:** What the next agent should work on
#
# This is how the next agent (or human) knows exactly where you
# stopped and what to do next. NEVER skip this step.